{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:21:36.455Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Every agent built in Python starts with naming values and knowing what kind of data each value is. Variables bind names to objects in memory; data types determine which operations are valid. This foundation prevents the subtle bugs that break tool calls, corrupt conversation state, and produce invalid API payloads."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "text": "variable", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a name that refers to an object stored in memory. Assignment with "}, {"type": "text", "text": "=", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " creates or rebinding that reference — it does not copy the object unless you explicitly ask for one."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "text": "data type", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " classifies an object and defines its behavior. Python is "}, {"type": "text", "text": "dynamically typed", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ": the type is determined at runtime from the assigned value, not from a declaration statement."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Core built-in types for agent code"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "str", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — text: prompts, model output, JSON as text"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "int", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — whole numbers: token counts, retry limits, indices"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "float", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — decimals: temperature, confidence scores, latencies"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "bool", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — "}, {"type": "text", "text": "True", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "text": "False", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ": feature flags, guard conditions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — sentinel for \"no value\": optional fields, missing tool results"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Agent systems constantly move data between prompts, parsers, tools, and persistence layers. A string token count ("}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"512\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ") behaves differently from an integer ("}, {"type": "text", "text": "512", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "). Mixing types causes "}, {"type": "text", "text": "TypeError", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " at runtime and silent logic errors when comparisons fail."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Correct typing at the value level — even before formal type hints — makes tool schemas, message dictionaries, and configuration objects reliable."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Clarity", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — descriptive names like "}, {"type": "text", "text": "max_tool_retries", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " document intent"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Safety", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — knowing mutability prevents accidental shared-state bugs"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Debuggability", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — "}, {"type": "text", "text": "type()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "text": "isinstance()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " quickly expose shape mismatches"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "API compatibility", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — LLM APIs expect specific JSON types; Python values must match"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dynamic typing flexibility", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " vs. runtime surprises when types change under the same name"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No compile-time checks", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — errors surface during execution unless you add type hints and static analysis later"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reference semantics", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — two names can refer to the same mutable object; changes through one name affect the other"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assignment and rebinding"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Name binds to an integer\nmax_tokens = 4096\n\n# Rebinding: name now refers to a different object\nmax_tokens = 8192\n\n# Multiple names, one object\nconfig_a = {\"model\": \"gpt-4o\"}\nconfig_b = config_a  # same dict object\nconfig_b[\"temperature\"] = 0.2  # visible through config_a too"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Naming rules and conventions"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "snake_case", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "text": "system_prompt", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "tool_call_id", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Start with a letter or underscore, not a digit"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Avoid Python keywords: "}, {"type": "text", "text": "class", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "def", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "async", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use UPPER_SNAKE for module-level constants: "}, {"type": "text", "text": "DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 30", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inspecting types"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "role = \"assistant\"\nprint(type(role))          # <class 'str'>\nprint(isinstance(role, str))  # True\n\n# Prefer isinstance over type() == ... (supports inheritance)\npayload = {\"content\": \"hello\"}\nprint(isinstance(payload, dict))  # True"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mutability preview"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scalars like "}, {"type": "text", "text": "int", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "float", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "bool", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", and "}, {"type": "text", "text": "str", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " are "}, {"type": "text", "text": "immutable", "marks": [{"type": "glossaryTerm", "attrs": {"definition": "Immutability means that once a value or object is created, it cannot be changed; any \"change\" creates a new value instead of modifying the original."}}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Container types (lists, dicts) are covered in the Collections topic; knowing this distinction matters when sharing agent state across steps."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use it"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use explicit conversion", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " when reading JSON or environment variables: "}, {"type": "text", "text": "int(os.environ[\"MAX_RETRIES\"])", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use ", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for optional values"}, {"type": "text", "text": " rather than magic strings like \"N/A\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use constants", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for values that must not change during a run"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Avoid", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " reusing one variable name for unrelated types in the same function — it obscures invariants and confuses static tools."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to implement"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Agent message — dict with string keys and values\nmessage = {\n    \"role\": \"user\",\n    \"content\": \"Summarize the log file.\",\n}\n\n# Generation settings — typed values ready for an API client\ntemperature = 0.3          # float\nmax_tokens = 1024          # int\nstream = False             # bool\n\n# Parse string env var safely\nimport os\nraw = os.environ.get(\"MAX_TURNS\", \"10\")\nmax_turns = int(raw)       # explicit conversion"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Examples"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Valid vs. invalid operations"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "token_count = 100\ntoken_count + 50        # 150 — valid\n\nlabel = \"tokens: \"\n# label + token_count     # TypeError — str + int\nlabel + str(token_count)  # \"tokens: 100\" — convert first"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-world example"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "An orchestration layer receives tool output as JSON. Numeric fields often arrive as strings. Before comparing against limits, convert explicitly:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "raw_result = {\"latency_ms\": \"842\", \"success\": \"true\"}\n\nlatency = int(raw_result[\"latency_ms\"])\nif latency > 500:\n    trigger_slow_tool_alert(latency)\n\n# Booleans from JSON strings need parsing — do not rely on truthiness of \"false\"\nsuccess = raw_result[\"success\"].lower() == \"true\""}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assuming JSON numbers are Python ints", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — they usually are, but parsed text fields may not be"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using ", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "is", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " to compare values"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — "}, {"type": "text", "text": "is", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " checks identity; use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "==", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for value equality (see Operators topic)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mutable default arguments", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — covered in Functions; a classic source of cross-request state leaks in agents"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Shadowing builtins", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — naming a variable "}, {"type": "text", "text": "list", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " or "}, {"type": "text", "text": "id", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " breaks built-in calls"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Name variables after "}, {"type": "text", "text": "what they represent", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", not their type: "}, {"type": "text", "text": "retry_count", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " not "}, {"type": "text", "text": "int1", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Convert at "}, {"type": "text", "text": "system boundaries", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (HTTP, env, files), then use native types internally"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "is None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " to test for missing values — "}, {"type": "text", "text": "== None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " works but is discouraged"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of variables as "}, {"type": "text", "text": "labels on boxes", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", not the boxes themselves. The label can be moved to a different box (rebinding). Multiple labels can point to the same box (aliases). For immutable boxes, \"changing\" the contents means getting a new box; for mutable ones, everyone sharing the label sees the change."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Variables are names; objects have types determined at runtime"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Agent code relies heavily on "}, {"type": "text", "text": "str", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "int", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "float", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "bool", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", and "}, {"type": "text", "text": "None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Convert external data explicitly before arithmetic or comparison"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mutability affects shared agent state — treat it as a design concern from the start"}]}]}]}]}}